Forward Propagation

Data moves from input to output.

Input
 ↓
Hidden Layer
 ↓
Hidden Layer
 ↓
Prediction
Loss Function

Measures how wrong the prediction is.

Examples:

Mean Squared Error (MSE)
Cross Entropy Loss

Smaller loss means better predictions.

Backpropagation

Backpropagation calculates how much each weight contributed to the error and updates the weights to reduce the loss.

Process:

Prediction
      ↓
Calculate Loss
      ↓
Backpropagation
      ↓
Update Weights
Gradient Descent

Gradient Descent updates weights to minimize the loss.

Update rule:

New Weight=Old Weight−Learning Rate×Gradient

The learning rate controls how large each update step is.

Epoch

One complete pass through the entire training dataset.

Example:

Dataset: 10,000 images
One epoch = training on all 10,000 images once
Batch Size

The number of training samples processed before updating the weights.

Example:

Dataset = 1000 images
Batch size = 100
Number of batches = 10
Common Neural Network Types
Artificial Neural Network (ANN) – Tabular data, simple prediction tasks.
Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) – Images, object detection, face recognition.
Recurrent Neural Network (RNN) – Sequential data like text and speech.
LSTM – A type of RNN that handles long-term dependencies better.
Transformer – Powers modern language models like ChatGPT.
Applications
Image recognition
Speech recognition
Machine translation
Chatbots
Self-driving cars
Medical diagnosis
Fraud detection
Recommendation systems
Advantages
Learns features automatically
Very accurate with large datasets
Excellent for images, audio, and text
Handles complex patterns
Disadvantages
Requires large amounts of data
Computationally expensive
Needs powerful hardware (GPUs)
Often difficult to interpret ("black box")
Machine Learning vs Deep Learning
Machine Learning	Deep Learning
Manual feature engineering	Automatic feature learning
Works well with smaller datasets	Performs best with large datasets
Faster to train	Slower to train
Lower computational cost	Higher computational cost
Simpler models	Multi-layer neural networks
